&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;My friend Ravi told me that we should wait for our friends.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;Direct Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;As per the given question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;The given sentence is an imperative sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;One can change the sentence by following the below rules.&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Let&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is used in a sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;to express a suggestion or proposal.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;We can infer it from the mood of the sentence if something is suggested or proposed&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;Reporting verbs such as &amp;quot;&amp;lsquo;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;said&amp;rsquo;, &amp;lsquo;told&amp;rsquo;, &amp;lsquo;said to&amp;rsquo;&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;change to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lsquo;proposed&amp;lsquo; or &amp;lsquo;suggested&amp;lsquo;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;Here the reporting clause and reported clause can be connected with the conjunction &amp;lsquo;that&amp;rsquo;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;Sometimes&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;to&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used. In that case, reporting verb &amp;lsquo;say to&amp;rsquo; changes to tell.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;We&amp;rsquo;/&amp;lsquo;us&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;pronouns change to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lsquo;they&amp;rsquo;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;If a first-person &amp;lsquo;I&amp;rsquo; is included then &amp;lsquo;we&amp;rsquo; or the mentioned pronoun remains unchanged.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;The modal auxiliary verb &amp;quot;should&amp;quot; is used in the reported clause.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot; user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Thus, by following the above rule, the correct sentence is:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;My friend Ravi told me that we should wait for our friends.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;unite&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot; display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;lsquo;&lt;strong&gt;alienate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo;(verb) means-&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;to make people feel that they cannot share your opinions anymore&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;. (अपने से दूर कर देना, अपनों को दूर कर देना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;E.g:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;The latest tax proposals will &lt;strong&gt;alienate &lt;/strong&gt;many voters.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s have a look at the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;meaning&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the words that are given in the options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;muddle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(verb)- &amp;ldquo;to put things in the wrong place or order or to make them untidy&amp;rdquo;. (&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;वस्&amp;zwj;तुओं को उलटा-सीधा रख देना या उन्&amp;zwj;हें गंदा कर देना&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;precipitate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(verb)- &amp;ldquo;to make something, especially something bad, happen suddenly or sooner than it should&amp;rdquo;. (&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;किसी घटना को विशेषतः प्रतिकूल घटना को&amp;nbsp;अचानक या समय से पूर्व घटित करना या होने देना&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;unite&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(verb)- &amp;ldquo;to join together and act in agreement; to make this happen&amp;rdquo;. (&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;जुड़ जाना और मिलकर काम करना; को&amp;nbsp;जोड़ देना और मिला देना&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;rummage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(verb)- &amp;ldquo;to move things and make them untidy while you are looking for something&amp;rdquo;.&amp;nbsp;(&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;कुछ ढूँढ़ते हुए चीज़ें इधर-उधर फैलाना&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lsquo;unite&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;correct antonym&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the given bold word.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the given word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;alienate&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;unite&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;combine&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;join&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;marry&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;disarm&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;,&amp;nbsp;etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;synonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the given word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;alienate&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are- &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;divide&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;divorce&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;part&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;separate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;,&amp;nbsp;etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;alienate&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; in a sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;an urban environment which would &lt;strong&gt;alienate &lt;/strong&gt;its inhabitants&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is Option (4) i.e.&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Under all circumstances&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Through thick and thin&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;means: In both good times and bad times (हर परिस्थिति में)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: She has supported me &lt;strong&gt;through thick and thin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Under all circumstances: &lt;/strong&gt;(हर स्थिति में) - Regardless of the situation or difficulty.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This option directly reflects the idiom&amp;#39;s meaning related to &lt;strong&gt;unwavering support or allegiance in every situation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Under all circumstances&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In winter and summer:&lt;/strong&gt; Literal seasons, not related to the abstract meaning of support and loyalty conveyed by the idiom.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In favourable situations:&lt;/strong&gt; (अनुकूल स्थितियों में) - Only when things are going well, which does not fully capture the idiom&amp;#39;s encompassing intent.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In crowded areas: &lt;/strong&gt;(भीड़-भाड़ वाले क्षेत्रों में) - A literal physical space, unrelated to the concept of enduring support implied by the idiom.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;epic.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Epic&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;means grand or heroic, which is the most appropriate word to fill the blank. (बहुत लंबा और उत्तेजना भरा)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;This is an &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;epic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; story.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Epic&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is the correct answer because it accurately conveys the intended meaning of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Correct passage:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the core of the &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;epic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; lies the fierce ______ (2) ______&amp;nbsp;between two branches of the Kuru dynasty, the Pandavas and the Kauravas. The lifelong struggle ______ (3) ______&amp;nbsp;the cousins for the throne of Hastinapur Culminates ______ (4) ______&amp;nbsp;bloody battle of Kurukshetra, in which ______ (5) ______&amp;nbsp;kings of that period participated and perished.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Bright&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is an adjective that describes something that is shining or colorful. (प्रकाश-भरा, प्रदीप्&amp;zwj;त, उज्ज्वल, चमकीला)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Exercise&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is a noun that refers to physical activity done to improve health or fitness. ((शरीर के) स्वस्थ एवं मज़बूत बनाने के लिए किया गया शारीरिक तथा मानसिक क्रियाकलाप; व्&amp;zwj;यायाम, कसरत)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Dull&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is an adjective that describes something that is boring or uninteresting. (अरुचिकर या अनुत्तेजक; उबाऊ)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;rivalry.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Rivalry&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means competition or conflict between two or more parties. (प्रतिद्वंद्वित, प्रतिस्&amp;zwj;पर्धा (व्&amp;zwj;यक्तियों, समूहों आदि में))&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is often used to describe a situation where two people, groups, or organizations are competing for the same thing.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;The &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;rivalry&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; between two companies in the same industry can be intense.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Correct passage:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;At the core of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;epic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;lies the fierce&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;rivalry&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;between two branches of the Kuru dynasty, the Pandavas and the Kauravas. The lifelong struggle ______ (3) ______&amp;nbsp;the cousins for the throne of Hastinapur Culminates ______ (4) ______&amp;nbsp;bloody battle of Kurukshetra, in which ______ (5) ______&amp;nbsp;kings of that period participated and perished.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Commute&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to travel regularly between one&amp;#39;s place of work and home. (प्रतिदिन निवास स्&amp;zwj;थान से कार्य-स्&amp;zwj;थान तक यात्रा करना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Hostile&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means unfriendly or aggressive. (व्&amp;zwj;यक्ति या वस्&amp;zwj;तु के प्रति अत्&amp;zwj;यंत उग्र भावनाओं वाला; प्रतिकूल भाव)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Friendship&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means a close relationship between two people based on mutual trust, affection, and support. (मित्रता; दोस्&amp;zwj;ती)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;between.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The blank refers to the &lt;strong&gt;conflict &lt;/strong&gt;that occurred &lt;strong&gt;between &lt;/strong&gt;the &lt;strong&gt;two &lt;/strong&gt;specific &lt;strong&gt;branches &lt;/strong&gt;of the Kuru dynasty, the &lt;strong&gt;Pandavas &lt;/strong&gt;and the &lt;strong&gt;Kauravas&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In such a context where the conflict is specifically mentioned between &lt;strong&gt;two defined groups&lt;/strong&gt;, the word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;between&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is the most appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;between&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is usually used when referring to the relationship or differentiation among two distinct entities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Correct passage:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;At the core of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;epic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;lies the fierce&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;rivalry&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;between two branches of the Kuru dynasty, the Pandavas and the Kauravas. The lifelong struggle&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;between&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;the cousins for the throne of Hastinapur Culminates ______ (4) ______&amp;nbsp;bloody battle of Kurukshetra, in which ______ (5) ______&amp;nbsp;kings of that period participated and perished.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Inside&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to something being contained within a space or object. (किसी वस्&amp;zwj;तु के अंदरूनी भाग या सतह में/पर/की ओर, के भीतर, के अंदर, अंदर या भीतर के)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;em&gt; The keys are &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;inside&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; the drawer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Amongst&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is used to describe something being in the midst of a group of people or things. (से घिरा हुआ; के बीच में)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;The bird was hiding &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;amongst&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; the leaves.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Along&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to something moving or extending in a particular direction or path. (के साथ-साथ, एक सिरे से दूसरे सिरे तक या की ओर)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;We walked &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;along&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; the beach.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;in the.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The preposition&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;in&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is followed by the article &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;the&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; to indicate a specific location or position.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;The sun sets &lt;u&gt;in the&lt;/u&gt; west.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In this context, the blank is referring to a physical location, so &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;in the&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is the most appropriate option.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Correct passage:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;At the core of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;epic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;lies the fierce&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;rivalry&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;between two branches of the Kuru dynasty, the Pandavas and the Kauravas. The lifelong struggle&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;between&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;the cousins for the throne of Hastinapur Culminates&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;in the&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;bloody battle of Kurukshetra, in which ______ (5) ______&amp;nbsp;kings of that period participated and perished.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;most.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Most&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is the appropriate option to fill in the blank.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It indicates a higher degree or quantity compared to the other options. ((संख्&amp;zwj;या या मात्रा में) अधिकतम)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;Who got the &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;most&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; points?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a superlative form of the word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;many&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;much.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is Option 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Correct passage:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;At the core of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;epic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;lies the fierce&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;rivalry&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;between two branches of the Kuru dynasty, the Pandavas and the Kauravas. The lifelong struggle&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;between&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;the cousins for the throne of Hastinapur Culminates&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;in the&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;bloody battle of Kurukshetra, in which &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;most&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; kings of that period participated and perished.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2, &amp;quot;each&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, refers to every individual item or person in a group. (प्रत्&amp;zwj;येक व्&amp;zwj;यक्ति या वस्&amp;zwj;तु)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3, &amp;quot;total&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, refers to the sum of all parts or numbers. (सबको गिनकर या मिलाकर बनी संख्&amp;zwj;या या मात्रा; पूर्ण)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4, &amp;quot;almost&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, means nearly or almost reaching a certain point or degree. (लगभग; क़रीब-क़रीब)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;In the question given below, a set of four sentences P, Q, R &amp;amp; S is given, which when properly sequenced, form a coherent paragraph. Arrange the sentences in the correct order and mark the correct order as your answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P. Over the past few years, India&amp;#39;s declining savings rate has been a puzzle for macroeconomists.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Q. However, fresh data from a survey shows that among urban India&amp;#39;s working population, the young employees tend to save a higher share of their incomes than their older counterparts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;R. Also, the savings patterns of post-millennials and millennials are similar, the data show.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S. Some have blamed slow rise in household incomes for this while others have suggested that younger Indians saving less than what their parents did may be to blame.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct order to form a coherent paragraph is: 3) &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;PSQR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct order for these sentences to form a coherent paragraph is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P. &lt;/strong&gt;Over the past few years, India&amp;#39;s declining savings rate has been a puzzle for macroeconomists.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S.&lt;/strong&gt; Some have blamed slow rise in household incomes for this while others have suggested that younger Indians saving less than what their parents did may be to blame.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Q.&lt;/strong&gt; However, fresh data from a survey shows that among urban India&amp;#39;s working population, the young employees tend to save a higher share of their incomes than their older counterparts.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;R.&lt;/strong&gt; Also, the savings patterns of post-millennials and millennials are similar, the data show.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This order forms a coherent paragraph as it first introduces the problem (P), then presents some hypotheses about the problem (S), next it introduces new data that contradicts one of the hypotheses (Q), and finally, it provides additional information about the new data (R).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The paragraph would be:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Over the past few years, India&amp;rsquo;s declining savings rate has been a puzzle for macroeconomists. Some have blamed slow rise in household incomes for this while others have suggested that younger Indians saving less than what their parents did may be to blame. However, fresh data from a survey shows that among urban India&amp;rsquo;s working population, the young employees tend to save a higher share of their incomes than their older counterparts. Also, the savings patterns of post-millennials and millennials are similar, the data show.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This question consists of six sentences of a passage. The first and sixth sentences are given as S1 and S6. The middle four sentences in each have been jumbled up and labelled as P, Q, R and S. You are required to find the proper sequence of the four sentences and mark your response accordingly.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S1: The United States is working a new round of sanctions against North Korea, U.S. National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan said on Thursday, as Pyongyang forges ahead with banned missile development and signals a possible new nuclear test.&lt;br /&gt;
P: Mr. Sullivan, who spoke via live video link, did not elaborate but said Washington was committed to using pressure and diplomacy to entice North Korea into giving up its nuclear arsenal.&lt;br /&gt;
Q: &amp;quot;We have a new set of sanctions measures coming forward as we speak,&amp;quot; he told a conference in Seoul organised by the U.S.-based Center for Strategic and International Studies and the South Korean JoongAng media group.&lt;br /&gt;
R: The &amp;quot;North Star&amp;quot; of U.S. Joe Biden&amp;#39;s North Korea policy is the denuclearisation of the Korean peninsula, and it remains steadfast in pursuing that goal while being flexible in working with partners on how to achieve it, he said.&lt;br /&gt;
S: He pointed to increased cooperation between the United States, South Korea, and Japan, which have increased joint military drills.&lt;br /&gt;
S6: The United States is also working on a more &amp;quot;visible&amp;quot; regional presence of its strategic assets, Mr. Sullivan said, referring to major weapons such as aircraft carriers and long-range bombers.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;QPRS&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S1&lt;/strong&gt; starts the passage stating the US&amp;#39;s intentions to sanction North Korea,&amp;nbsp;substantiated by US NSA Jake Sullivan.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A quote from Sullivan follows in Part &lt;strong&gt;Q&lt;/strong&gt; which states explicitly that a new set of sanctions was underway. It also provides the location of the conference as being Seoul in South Korea.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Part &lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt; follows some more details of Sullivan&amp;#39;s comments not elaborating but telling that Washington was committed in using pressure and diplomacy in enticing North Korea to give up its nuclear arsenal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The next in sequence is part &lt;strong&gt;R&lt;/strong&gt; which describes US President Joe Biden&amp;#39;s North Korea policy, which states its main objective of denuclearising the Korean peninsula remaining steadfast in pursuing that goal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Part &lt;strong&gt;S&lt;/strong&gt; follows and provides additional information about cooperation between US, South Korea and Japan to achieve that above mentioned goal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S6&lt;/strong&gt; concludes the passage with the US described as working on a more visible regional presence of its strategic assets, by Mr. Sullivan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct passage is&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; :&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The United States is working a new round of sanctions against North Korea, U.S. National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan said on Thursday, as Pyongyang forges ahead with banned missile development and signals a possible new nuclear test. Q&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;We have a new set of sanctions measures coming forward as we speak,&amp;quot; he told a conference in Seoul organised by the U.S.-based Center for Strategic and International Studies and the South Korean JoongAng media group. &lt;strong&gt;P&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Mr. Sullivan, who spoke via live video link, did not elaborate but said Washington was committed to using pressure and diplomacy to entice North Korea into giving up its nuclear arsenal.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;R&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The &amp;quot;North Star&amp;quot; of U.S. Joe Biden&amp;#39;s North Korea policy is the denuclearisation of the Korean peninsula, and it remains steadfast in pursuing that goal while being flexible in working with partners on how to achieve it, he said. &lt;strong&gt;S&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;He pointed to increased cooperation between the United States, South Korea, and Japan, which have increased joint military drills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;The United States is also working on a more &amp;quot;visible&amp;quot; regional presence of its strategic assets, Mr. Sullivan said, referring to major weapons such as aircraft carriers and long-range bombers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
